metadata.name: Diversity Flow - fxhash  #1
metadata.description:
Diversity Flows – fxhash edition
An abstract expressionist collection created with code.
 
- This collection is an homage to all facets of diversity, and the importance of recognising, respecting and valuing differences. 

- The artworks were created by combining a generative flowfield algorithm with atypical shapes and forms in order to render very diverse but organic looking textures and effects. Over 50 different palettes were used, leading to very distinct-looking unique artworks.

- The algorithms were coded and run in R (The R Project for Statistical Computing, #rstats) and ported to fxhash as png images via p5js. Higher resolution images are available upon request.

Created by @1Abstract_1 (twitter handle)
https://linktr.ee/1Abstract

metadata.name: The Smoothest Cube Over The Number Three #18
metadata.description:
An infinite experiential soundtrack composed of three notes and three hues. The smoothest cube oscillates between long notes and staccato noise to render a true glitch piece.

The tone and light palette uses a loose adaptation of the Scriabin note to color correspondence. His synesthesia allowed him to perceive color as sounds and he developed a correspondence between pitch and hue with a notable bias for blues and reds.

[click - touch]  Start animation and awesome sounds
[space]          Pause animation as the last note sinks in
[s]              Save PNG file

Artwork by @0xphiiil

metadata.name: Impending Cloths #76
metadata.description:
IC makes use of fabric's potential for contrasts.
The same piece of cloth can seem to be falling, perfectly still and ready to be blown away, all at the same time.
It can look "very digital" while also achieving a high degree of texture. And so on, and so forth. Contrast and potential.
Also, "h" can be pressed to download in high resolution, although it may take up to a minute.

metadata.name: Room of Imagination #20
metadata.description:
"Is this the real life?

Is this just fantasy?"

Room of Imagination is an exercise of fantasy, where a room of our creative mind comes true.

The colors and elements convey sensations and the final result conveys the feeling.


The Rooms of Imagination are layered artworks generated from a pool of previously rendered digital furniture.

metadata.name: Penumbra #11
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)

metadata.name: miniGlyph #96
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers
